h3. Problem definition

The [Migrating from Cloud to Server applications|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver071/migrating-from-jira-cloud-to-server-applications-802592270.html] documentation, mentions the following under the 3rd step " Import your JIRA Cloud application data into your JIRA Server application" :
{quote:}
Follow the instructions in on the setup wizard until you have configured a database (described in step 1 of Running the setup wizard). If you already have some data in your JIRA application installation, this step will overwrite it.
In step 2 of the setup wizard (Application Properties),  you will be asked whether you have existing data. Click import your existing data and follow the instructions to import the JIRA Cloud application backup that you generated earlier. Note, you may see the following message. This is a warning only, your import will still work.
{quote}  

This causes some confusion for the users as they expect that the import can only be performed during the set up and stage and not after.

h3. Suggested Solution

Inform the user clearly that they are able to Restore the backup even after the Set up stages as per the [Restoring data from an XML Backup|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver071/restoring-data-from-an-xml-backup-802592998.html]

