JIRA Core 7.x

When use
 * Time Tracking is currently *ON*
 * Time estimates will be displayed in the following format: *hours (e.g. 36.5h)*.

Real display *1h 11m NOT 1.18h* 

In Method com.atlassian.jira.util.JiraDurationUtils.calculateFractionalTimeUnit
{code:java}
durationBD.setScale(scale.scale, RoundingMode.UNNECESSARY).divide(secondsPerUnitBD).setScale(scale.scale, RoundingMode.UNNECESSARY);{code}
return ArithmeticException when calculate 4260L secons( = 1h*(60*60) + 11m*(60))

I Use workaround : 
{code:java}
BigDecimal.valueOf(durationBD.doubleValue() / secondsPerUnitBD.doubleValue()).setScale(scale.scale, RoundingMode.HALF_EVEN);{code}

